Subject: some subject
Content-Type: text/x-markdown
Alias: what-to-display-in-url
Tags: tag1,tag2,tag3

1. Subject: is the title of the blog.

2. Content-Type: defines the type of encoding used in the article source.

    There are three encoding types supported:

     - text/plain
     - text/html
     - text/x-markdown

    If not supplied but the first characters is a <, it becomes text/html.

3. Alias: defines the name that will be used for naming the article's perma-link.

4. Tags: is a comma separated list of tags that are associated with the article.

